## Svelte 5 Patterns

### State
```svelte
<script lang="ts">
let count = $state(0);
</script>
```

### Props
```svelte
<script lang="ts">
interface Props {
  title: string;
  onClick?: () => void;
}
let { title, onClick }: Props = $props();
</script>
```

### Effects
```svelte
<script lang="ts">
$effect(() => {
  console.log('count changed:', count);
});
</script>
```

## File Organization

- `src/routes/` - Pages and API routes
- `src/lib/components/` - Reusable components (PascalCase.svelte)
- `src/lib/components/ui/` - UI library components
- `src/lib/types.ts` - Shared TypeScript types
- `src/lib/server/` - Server-only code

## Biome

Handles formatting and linting. Run `bun run lint` before committing.

**Important**: Never run `--unsafe` without approval (can cause false positives on Svelte imports).

## Before Committing

1. Check for compilation errors in dev server
2. Run `bun run check` for TypeScript
3. Run `bun run lint` for Biome
4. Test the feature manually

